On Monday, October 23, 2006, at 05:28PM, <Neal354(-at-)wmconnect.com> wrote:

>                                                to remove the axles from the 
>transmission what size tool to I buy to remove the bolts.

Sometimes require an 8mm triple square (XZN) and sometimes it takes a hex (Allen) bit. Check before you buy.

Notes: the heads on these socket head screws can strip after 25 years if you don't get the heads clean before you try to undo them.

